---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="The Gut Barrier — Tight Junctions, Zonulin & Leaky Gut | Lifelong Athletics" description="Understanding tight junctions, zonulin, and leaky gut syndrome. The damage cascade, the repair protocol, and what to tell clients with food sensitivities. ACE · NASM · NSCA exam reference.">

<div class="gb-back-bar">
  <a href="/exam-prep" class="gb-back-link">← Back to Study Hub</a>
</div>

<style is:global>

  .gb-back-bar { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 110px 60px 0; }
  .gb-back-link {
    font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.12em; text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--muted); text-decoration: none; display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center; gap: 8px; transition: color 0.2s;
  }
  .gb-back-link:hover { color: var(--gold); }

  .gb-wrap * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

  .gb-wrap h1 { font-size: 36px; font-weight: 600; color: #ffd700; letter-spacing: -1px; }
  .gb-wrap h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 600; color: #ffd700; margin: 1.5rem 0 1rem; }
  .gb-wrap h3 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 600; color: #e0e0e0; }
  .gb-wrap p  { font-size: 14px; line-height: 1.7; color: #bbb; }

  .gb-wrap .infographic {
    font-family: 'Segoe UI', Tahoma, Geneva, sans-serif;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0f0f0f 0%, #1a1a1a 50%, #0f0f0f 100%);
    color: #e0e0e0;
    min-height: 100vh;
    padding: 3rem 2rem;
  }

  .gb-wrap .container { max-width: 1200px; margin: 0 auto; }

  .gb-wrap .hero {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 3rem;
    animation: gb-fadeInDown 0.8s ease-out;
  }
  .gb-wrap .hero h1 {
    font-size: 42px;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, #ffd700, #ffed4e);
    -webkit-background-clip: text;
    -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
    background-clip: text;
  }
  .gb-wrap .hero p {
    font-size: 16px;
    color: #999;
    max-width: 600px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .gb-wrap .junction-visual { margin: 2rem auto; text-align: center; }
  .gb-wrap .tight-junctions {
    display: inline-flex;
    gap: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    background: rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.05);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 12px;
    animation: gb-slideUp 0.8s ease-out 0.2s both;
  }
  .gb-wrap .junction {
    width: 60px;
    height: 60px;
    border: 3px solid #ffd700;
    border-radius: 8px;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    font-size: 28px;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    position: relative;
  }
  .gb-wrap .junction:after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    border: 2px solid #ffd700;
    border-radius: 8px;
    animation: gb-pulse 2s ease-in-out infinite;
    opacity: 0;
  }
  .gb-wrap .junction.sealed { background: rgba(81, 207, 102, 0.2); border-color: #51cf66; }
  .gb-wrap .junction.sealed:after { border-color: #51cf66; }
  .gb-wrap .junction.open { background: rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.2); border-color: #ff6b6b; }
  .gb-wrap .junction.open:after { border-color: #ff6b6b; }

  .gb-wrap .section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.02);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.15);
    border-radius: 12px;
    overflow: hidden;
    animation: gb-slideUp 0.8s ease-out both;
  }
  .gb-wrap .section:nth-child(1) { animation-delay: 0.2s; }
  .gb-wrap .section:nth-child(2) { animation-delay: 0.3s; }
  .gb-wrap .section:nth-child(3) { animation-delay: 0.4s; }
  .gb-wrap .section:nth-child(4) { animation-delay: 0.5s; }
  .gb-wrap .section:nth-child(5) { animation-delay: 0.6s; }

  .gb-wrap .section-header {
    padding: 1.5rem;
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.1) 0%, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.05) 100%);
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.2);
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  .gb-wrap .section-header:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(90deg, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.15) 0%, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.1) 100%);
  }
  .gb-wrap .section-title {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 12px;
    font-size: 18px;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #ffd700;
  }
  .gb-wrap .section-icon { font-size: 24px; }
  .gb-wrap .toggle-icon { font-size: 20px; transition: transform 0.3s ease; color: #ffd700; }
  .gb-wrap .section.expanded .toggle-icon { transform: rotate(180deg); }
  .gb-wrap .section-content {
    max-height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
    transition: max-height 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }
  .gb-wrap .section.expanded .section-content {
    max-height: 2000px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }

  .gb-wrap .grid-2 {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }
  .gb-wrap .grid-3 {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
  }

  .gb-wrap .card {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.08) 0%, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.02) 100%);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }
  .gb-wrap .card:hover {
    background: linear-gradient(135deg, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.12) 0%, rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.05) 100%);
    border-color: rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.4);
    transform: translateY(-4px);
  }
  .gb-wrap .card-icon { font-size: 32px; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; display: block; }
  .gb-wrap .card-title { font-size: 15px; font-weight: 600; color: #ffd700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .gb-wrap .card-text  { font-size: 12px; color: #aaa; line-height: 1.6; }

  .gb-wrap .cascade {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .gb-wrap .cascade-box {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 150px;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.04);
    border: 0.5px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 6px;
    text-align: center;
    font-size: 12px;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .gb-wrap .cascade-box.danger  { border-color: rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.4); background: rgba(255, 107, 107, 0.05); }
  .gb-wrap .cascade-box.warning { border-color: rgba(255, 146, 43, 0.4);  background: rgba(255, 146, 43, 0.05); }
  .gb-wrap .cascade-label { font-weight: 600; color: #ffd700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-size: 11px; text-transform: uppercase; }
  .gb-wrap .cascade-arrow { font-size: 24px; color: #ffd700; animation: gb-bounce 1.5s infinite; }

  .gb-wrap .feature-list { list-style: none; margin: 1rem 0; }
  .gb-wrap .feature-list li {
    padding: 0.75rem 0 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    position: relative;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: #bbb;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }
  .gb-wrap .feature-list li:before { content: '→'; position: absolute; left: 0; color: #ffd700; font-weight: 600; }
  .gb-wrap .damage-list  li:before { content: '✗'; color: #ff6b6b; }
  .gb-wrap .healing-list li:before { content: '✓'; color: #51cf66; }

  .gb-wrap .stats-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(180px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }
  .gb-wrap .stat-box {
    background: rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.2);
    border-radius: 8px;
    padding: 1.5rem;
    text-align: center;
  }
  .gb-wrap .stat-number { font-size: 28px; font-weight: 700; color: #ffd700; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
  .gb-wrap .stat-label  { font-size: 12px; color: #aaa; text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.5px; }

  .gb-wrap .protocol-step {
    background: rgba(81, 207, 102, 0.08);
    border-left: 3px solid #51cf66;
    padding: 1.25rem;
    margin: 1rem 0;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }
  .gb-wrap .protocol-step h4 {
    color: #51cf66;
    font-size: 13px;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
  }
  .gb-wrap .protocol-step p { font-size: 13px; color: #bbb; margin: 0; }

  .gb-wrap .btn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 0.75rem 1.5rem;
    background: rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.1);
    border: 0.5px solid rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.3);
    color: #ffd700;
    border-radius: 6px;
    cursor: pointer;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
    margin: 0.5rem;
  }
  .gb-wrap .btn:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.2);
    border-color: rgba(255, 215, 0, 0.5);
    transform: translateY(-2px);
  }

  @keyframes gb-pulse {
    0%, 100% { transform: scale(1); opacity: 1; }
    50%       { transform: scale(1.1); opacity: 0; }
  }
  @keyframes gb-bounce {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateX(0); }
    50%       { transform: translateX(6px); }
  }
  @keyframes gb-fadeInDown {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(-20px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }
  @keyframes gb-slideUp {
    from { opacity: 0; transform: translateY(30px); }
    to   { opacity: 1; transform: translateY(0); }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .gb-wrap .tight-junctions { flex-wrap: wrap; }
    .gb-wrap .grid-2, .gb-wrap .grid-3 { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .gb-wrap .cascade { flex-direction: column; }
    .gb-wrap h1 { font-size: 28px; }
  }
</style>

<div class="gb-wrap">
<div class="infographic">
  <div class="container">

    <!-- HERO -->
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>The Gut Barrier</h1>
      <p>Understanding tight junctions, zonulin, and leaky gut syndrome</p>
      <div class="junction-visual">
        <div class="tight-junctions">
          <div class="junction sealed">🔒</div>
          <div class="junction sealed">🔒</div>
          <div class="junction sealed">🔒</div>
          <div class="junction sealed">🔒</div>
          <div class="junction sealed">🔒</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHAT IS A TIGHT JUNCTION? -->
    <div class="section expanded">
      <div class="section-header" onclick="gbToggleSection(this)">
        <div class="section-title">
          <span class="section-icon">🔐</span>
          <span>What Is a Tight Junction?</span>
        </div>
        <span class="toggle-icon">▼</span>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content">
        <p><strong>Tight junctions are protein complexes that seal the gaps between intestinal cells.</strong> They act like a security checkpoint, controlling what enters your bloodstream and what stays out.</p>
        <div class="grid-2">
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🧬</span>
            <div class="card-title">Key Proteins</div>
            <div class="card-text">Claudins, occludin, and JAM (junctional adhesion molecules) lock intestinal cells together.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">✅</span>
            <div class="card-title">What Passes Through</div>
            <div class="card-text">Amino acids, glucose, minerals, vitamins. Small, digested nutrients only.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🚫</span>
            <div class="card-title">What Stays Out</div>
            <div class="card-text">Undigested food, bacteria, endotoxins (LPS), toxins, large molecules.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🛡️</span>
            <div class="card-title">Intestinal Epithelium</div>
            <div class="card-text">Single layer of cells (enterocytes) with tight junctions as the gatekeepers.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE KEY MOLECULE: ZONULIN -->
    <div class="section expanded">
      <div class="section-header" onclick="gbToggleSection(this)">
        <div class="section-title">
          <span class="section-icon">🔑</span>
          <span>The Key Molecule: Zonulin</span>
        </div>
        <span class="toggle-icon">▼</span>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content">
        <p><strong>Zonulin is a protein that literally opens tight junctions, acting like a key that unlocks the gates.</strong> When zonulin levels rise, gaps appear between intestinal cells. When it's low, junctions stay sealed.</p>
        <div class="cascade">
          <div class="cascade-box">
            <div class="cascade-label">Low Zonulin</div>
            <div>Tight junctions SEALED. Strong barrier. Normal digestion.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cascade-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="cascade-box warning">
            <div class="cascade-label">Rising Zonulin</div>
            <div>Junctions START to open. Small gaps appear. Trouble begins.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="cascade-arrow">→</div>
          <div class="cascade-box danger">
            <div class="cascade-label">High Zonulin</div>
            <div>Junctions WIDE OPEN. Large gaps. Leaky gut begins.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p style="margin-top: 1rem; font-style: italic; color: #999;">Zonulin is released by intestinal cells in response to stress, gluten (in sensitive individuals), inflammation, and dysbiosis.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- WHAT DAMAGES TIGHT JUNCTIONS -->
    <div class="section expanded">
      <div class="section-header" onclick="gbToggleSection(this)">
        <div class="section-title">
          <span class="section-icon">⚠️</span>
          <span>What Damages Tight Junctions?</span>
        </div>
        <span class="toggle-icon">▼</span>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content">
        <p>Multiple factors can trigger zonulin release and damage the intestinal barrier. The more factors present, the worse the damage.</p>
        <div class="grid-3">
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🌾</span>
            <div class="card-title">Gluten</div>
            <div class="card-text">Triggers zonulin in sensitive individuals. Creates strong inflammatory response.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">💊</span>
            <div class="card-title">NSAIDs</div>
            <div class="card-text">Ibuprofen, naproxen directly damage intestinal lining. Major trigger.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🧂</span>
            <div class="card-title">Processed Foods</div>
            <div class="card-text">Emulsifiers, food dyes, additives trigger inflammation and zonulin.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🍺</span>
            <div class="card-title">Excessive Alcohol</div>
            <div class="card-text">Damages intestinal cells directly. Disrupts microbiome.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">😰</span>
            <div class="card-title">Chronic Stress</div>
            <div class="card-text">High cortisol elevates zonulin. Impairs immune barrier.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">😴</span>
            <div class="card-title">Poor Sleep</div>
            <div class="card-text">Dysregulates tight junction proteins. Impairs repair.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🦠</span>
            <div class="card-title">Dysbiosis</div>
            <div class="card-text">Bad bacteria overgrowth. Produces inflammatory compounds.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">📈</span>
            <div class="card-title">High Sugar</div>
            <div class="card-text">Feeds pathogenic bacteria. Causes inflammation.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <span class="card-icon">🏃</span>
            <div class="card-title">Overtraining</div>
            <div class="card-text">Excessive exercise without recovery. Chronic cortisol elevation.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- THE CASCADE: FROM TIGHT TO LEAKY -->
    <div class="section expanded">
      <div class="section-header" onclick="gbToggleSection(this)">
        <div class="section-title">
          <span class="section-icon">🌊</span>
          <span>The Cascade: From Healthy to Leaky</span>
        </div>
        <span class="toggle-icon">▼</span>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content">
        <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Stage 1: Junctions Begin to Open</h3>
          <div class="cascade">
            <div class="cascade-box">
              <div class="cascade-label">Trigger</div>
              <div>Stress, gluten, NSAIDs, etc.</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cascade-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="cascade-box warning">
              <div class="cascade-label">Response</div>
              <div>Zonulin released by enterocytes</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cascade-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="cascade-box warning">
              <div class="cascade-label">Effect</div>
              <div>Claudins/occludin contract. Small gaps appear.</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Stage 2: Leaky Barrier (LPS Enters Bloodstream)</h3>
          <div class="cascade">
            <div class="cascade-box warning">
              <div class="cascade-label">What Leaks</div>
              <div>LPS (bacterial endotoxin), undigested food particles</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cascade-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="cascade-box danger">
              <div class="cascade-label">Immune Response</div>
              <div>Immune cells recognize LPS as a threat</div>
            </div>
            <div class="cascade-arrow">→</div>
            <div class="cascade-box danger">
              <div class="cascade-label">Inflammation</div>
              <div>Systemic inflammation, cytokine release, immune attack</div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">Stage 3: Symptoms & Complications</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list" style="list-style: none; padding: 0;">
            <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0;"><strong style="color: #ffd700;">Food sensitivities:</strong> IgG antibodies to foods you previously tolerated</li>
            <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0;"><strong style="color: #ffd700;">Brain fog & fatigue:</strong> LPS crosses blood-brain barrier (via leaky BBB)</li>
            <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0;"><strong style="color: #ffd700;">Autoimmune risk:</strong> Molecular mimicry — immune attacks self-tissues</li>
            <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0;"><strong style="color: #ffd700;">Malabsorption:</strong> Damaged enterocytes can't absorb nutrients properly</li>
            <li style="padding: 0.5rem 0;"><strong style="color: #ffd700;">Chronic inflammation:</strong> Low-grade endotoxemia (LPS in blood) 24/7</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- HEALING: THE REPAIR PROTOCOL -->
    <div class="section expanded">
      <div class="section-header" onclick="gbToggleSection(this)">
        <div class="section-title">
          <span class="section-icon">🌱</span>
          <span>Healing: The Repair Protocol</span>
        </div>
        <span class="toggle-icon">▼</span>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content">
        <p><strong>Gut barrier repair takes 4-8 weeks with proper nutrition and trigger removal.</strong> The three pillars: Remove, Restore, Rebuild.</p>
        <div style="margin: 2rem 0;">
          <h3 style="color: #ff6b6b; margin-bottom: 1rem;">🚫 REMOVE (Eliminate Triggers)</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list damage-list">
            <li>Gluten (for at least 30 days)</li>
            <li>NSAIDs (switch to acetaminophen temporarily)</li>
            <li>Processed foods & additives</li>
            <li>Excess alcohol</li>
            <li>High-stress activities (intense cardio without recovery)</li>
            <li>Sleep better (7-9 hours nightly)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="margin: 2rem 0;">
          <h3 style="color: #51cf66; margin-bottom: 1rem;">✓ RESTORE (Provide Building Blocks)</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list healing-list">
            <li><strong>L-Glutamine:</strong> Favourite fuel of enterocytes. 5-10g daily.</li>
            <li><strong>Zinc:</strong> Essential for tight junction proteins. 15-30mg daily.</li>
            <li><strong>Bone Broth:</strong> Collagen, gelatin, amino acids. 1-2 cups daily.</li>
            <li><strong>Omega-3s:</strong> Anti-inflammatory. Supports barrier integrity.</li>
            <li><strong>Vitamin D:</strong> Regulates zonulin. 2000-4000 IU daily.</li>
            <li><strong>Aloe Vera:</strong> Soothes and heals intestinal lining.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="margin: 2rem 0;">
          <h3 style="color: #ffd700; margin-bottom: 1rem;">🔄 REBUILD (Restore Microbiome)</h3>
          <ul class="feature-list healing-list">
            <li><strong>Fermented foods:</strong> Sauerkraut, kimchi, kefir, tempeh (probiotics)</li>
            <li><strong>Fibre:</strong> Feeds good bacteria (prebiotic). 25-35g daily.</li>
            <li><strong>Resistant starch:</strong> Cooled cooked potatoes, green bananas.</li>
            <li><strong>Polyphenols:</strong> Berries, green tea (feed good bugs)</li>
            <li><strong>Avoid antibiotics:</strong> Unless absolutely necessary (kills good bacteria too)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div style="margin: 2rem 0;">
          <h3 style="color: #ffd700; margin-bottom: 1rem;">Timeline:</h3>
          <div class="protocol-step">
            <h4>Weeks 1-2: Remove Triggers</h4>
            <p>Cut out gluten, NSAIDs, processed foods. Start L-glutamine, zinc, bone broth. Rest and sleep more.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="protocol-step">
            <h4>Weeks 2-4: Restore & Reduce Inflammation</h4>
            <p>Continue removal. Add fermented foods. Enterocytes begin regeneration. Zonulin starts dropping.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="protocol-step">
            <h4>Weeks 4-8: Rebuild Microbiome</h4>
            <p>Good bacteria repopulate. Tight junctions reseal. Inflammation drops. Symptoms improve.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="protocol-step">
            <h4>Weeks 8+: Maintenance</h4>
            <p>Reintroduce foods slowly. Monitor tolerance. Maintain healthy gut habits for life.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- BY THE NUMBERS -->
    <div class="section expanded">
      <div class="section-header" onclick="gbToggleSection(this)">
        <div class="section-title">
          <span class="section-icon">📊</span>
          <span>By the Numbers</span>
        </div>
        <span class="toggle-icon">▼</span>
      </div>
      <div class="section-content">
